<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="526" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="129.[152,1361,1632,2610]" pageId="129" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[153,510,2419,2452]" pageId="129" pageNumber="526">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Bates’s White-toothed Shrew is considered uncommon or rare throughout much ofits distribution, although it has a wide distribution and does not seem to face any major threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
